1.title: Flume-Igation/On the Poolfront
1.plot: On the hottest day of the year, Mort Weinerman is able to build Randy and Howard's dream pool.

2.title: Welcome Back Catfish/All the Juice That's Fish to Swim
2.plot: Randy gets McFist tossed from the chillest island resort on Lake LaRusso. Howard has to go to the center of the Earth to set the fart record straight.

3.title: Julian's Birthday Surprise/True Bromance
3.plot: Randy brings the Sorcerer's Ball to Julian's magic-themed birthday party.

4.title: Unstank My Hart/Whoopee 2: The Wrath of Whoopee 2
4.plot: Levander Hart is still angry at Randy and Howard for kicking him out of 30 Seconds to Math and is plotting his revenge.

5.title: M-M-M-My Bologna/Everybody Ninj-Along
5.plot: Randy and Howard must take care of a bologna "baby" for science class.

6.title: Fudge Factory/Best Buds
6.plot: Randy makes up a fake fudge factory and puts both Howard and himself in grave danger.

7.title: Otto Know Better/Brolateral Damage
7.plot: When Randy finds and falls in love with Viceroy's beloved "pet" Otto, he refuses to give it back, inadvertently putting Norrisville in danger.

8.title: Let the Wonk One In/The Curse of Mudfart
8.plot: A camping trip goes wrong after Randy tells the horror story of mudfar and ends up he does exist

9.title: Shoot First, Ask Questions Laser/Ninjception
9.plot: Randy and Howard decide to use Ninja-ing to even the laser tag playing field. Stuck in a dream-within-a-dream-within-a-dream, Randy must figure out how to escape the loop.

10.title: Happy Hanukkah, Howard Weinerman!/Snow-Klahoma!
10.plot: Howard must save Greg's Game Hole and learn the true meaning of Hanukkah. Randy purposely leaves the Nomicon at school so Ninja-ing won't ruin his trip with Howard to Sno-klahoma.

11.title: Randy Cunningham's Day Off/Bro-ing Down the House
11.plot: Randy and Howard break in to Mcfist's Mansion and the Mansion turns out to be super fun, will they make an exit?

12.title: Living in Shooblivion/McNinja - Brought to You by McFist
12.plot: Distracted by the "Ninja Fails Live" webcast, Randy seeks the help of the blind sword smith of Norrisville. Ninja sells out and endorses every business in Norrisville.

13.title: Mastermind of Disastermind/The Brawn also Rises
13.plot: Howard sets out to prove that he is a true "mastermind" that could defeat the Ninja. Randy and Howard's fake "Chuck-a-Cabra" video draws the attention of monster hunter.

14.title: Debbie Meddle/Aplopalypse Now
14.plot: Student journalist Debbie Kang may have evidence that Randy is the Ninja. Randy nearly causes a catastrophe by treating an ancient guardian with a day on the town.

15.title: Rory: Hero of a Past/Mort-al Combat
15.plot: Viceroy has been ripping off a cheesy '80s cartoon for all of his bot designs. Howard's dad Mort thinks Ninja is out to get him, leading to an epic Mort vs. Ninja battle!

16.title: Wonkin' for the Weekend/Ninjafan
16.plot: Contaminated McBubbleSlam accidentally turns Howard into an A+ student. When Ninja leads on an admirer, he ends up turning his super-fan into a stanked fan.

17.title: When Howie Met Randy/Bro Money Bro Problems
17.plot: 6-year-old Randy tries to convince new kid Howard that Norrisville has a Ninja. Randy and Howard unwittingly sell used Ninja weapons to Viceroy.

18.title: The Three Mascoteers/Escape from Scrap City
18.plot: Howard is chosen to be the new school mascot. Ninja and McFist must work side by side if they want any hope of escaping the ruthless bots of Scrap City!

19.title: Space Cow Bros/The Fresh Principal of Norrisville High
19.plot: Randy accidentally launches Howard into space with a killer robot aboard the shuttle! Randy and Howard get Slimovitz fired and a computer-based program takes his place.

20.title: The Prophecy of Hat Sword/Fake Fight for Your Right to Party
20.plot: Principal Slimovitz threatens to split Randy and Howard up unless they improve their grades. Randy and Howard get kicked out of a party and go overboard trying to get back in.

21.title: McCluckerbusters/Let Them Eat Cake Fries
21.plot: Randy and Howard inadvertently start a war that threatens to destroy their two favorite eateries forever! Slimovitz removes cake-fries from the Norrisville High menu.

22.title: Club Ninja-dise/To Smell and Back
22.plot: Randy gets McFist tossed from the chillest island resort on Lake LaRusso. Howard has to go to the center of the Earth to set the fart record straight.

23.title: Big Trouble in Little Norrisville/Winner Takes Ball
23.plot: Randy and Howard come across a Sorcerer's Ball on a field trip to Little Norrisville. Randy accidentally sends Howard on a quest for the final Sorcerer's Ball.

24.title: Ball's Well That Friends Well
24.plot: Randy discovers that his family is moving because Norrisville has become too dangerous, so he decides that he must defeat Cyborg Julian and make his town a safe place to live.
